<item>
            <title>[LU-19765] High latency in Lustre operations and Permission Denied errors due to Identity Upcall timeouts (rc = -110)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19765</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On a Lustre 2.17.0 cluster, metadata operations (mount, unmount, touch) are experiencing extreme delays (2&#8211;4 minutes). While &lt;tt&gt;root&lt;/tt&gt; can eventually complete a &lt;tt&gt;touch&lt;/tt&gt;, non-root users receive &quot;Permission denied&quot; after a significant hang.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Setting &lt;tt&gt;identity_upcall&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;NONE&lt;/tt&gt; bypasses the delay and restores normal performance, indicating a bottleneck or failure in the &lt;tt&gt;l_getidentity_nss&lt;/tt&gt; upcall path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Environment&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Environment&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Lustre Version:&lt;/b&gt; 2.17.0_RC4_4_g81318f8&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Upcall Configuration:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;tt&gt;mdt.* MDT*.identity_upcall=/usr/sbin/l_getidentity_nss&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Identity Source:&lt;/b&gt; Remote LDAP via NSS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Symptoms&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Symptoms&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;1. Metadata Latency:&lt;/b&gt; ** A &lt;tt&gt;touch&lt;/tt&gt; as root takes over 4 minutes&lt;b&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# time touch /lus/fs_name/test_file
real    4m1.679s
user    0m0.001s
sys     0m0.000s &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;2. Permission Denied for Non-Root:&lt;/b&gt; ** Users encounter &lt;tt&gt;EACCES&lt;/tt&gt; after a ~2-minute timeout:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
$ time touch /lus/fs_name/user_file
touch: cannot touch &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;/lus/fs_name/user_file&apos;&lt;/span&gt;: Permission denied
real    2m1.124s &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;3. MDS Kernel Errors:&lt;/b&gt; The MDS nodes report upcall cache acquisition failures with error &lt;tt&gt;-110&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
LustreError: [PID]:0:(upcall_cache.c:342:upcall_cache_get_entry()) [FS]-MDT0000: acquire &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; key [UID] after 30: rc = -110 &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;tt&gt;rc = -110&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;upcall_cache_get_entry&lt;/tt&gt; suggests that the Lustre MDS is successfully triggering the upcall, but the user space process (&lt;tt&gt;l_getidentity_nss&lt;/tt&gt;) is failing to return identity/group information within the 30-second window.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;StepstoReproduce&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Steps to Reproduce&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Configure Lustre MDT to use &lt;tt&gt;/usr/sbin/l_getidentity_nss&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ensure an LDAP-backed NSS configuration is active on the MDS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Perform metadata operations from a client.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Observe &lt;tt&gt;rc = -110&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;dmesg&lt;/tt&gt; on the MDS and high &lt;tt&gt;real&lt;/tt&gt; time on the client.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
