                            <comment id="484924" author="JIRAUSER18804" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2026 04:37:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;from @zam&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After setting upcall to /usr/sbin/l_getidentity performed the mount, touch and file operations as root and non-root users all operations are back to normal there is no delay or permission denied issues.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# pdsh -g mds lctl get_param mdt.*-MDT*.identity_upcall
mdt.*.identity_upcall=/usr/sbin/l_getidentity
mdt.*.identity_upcall=/usr/sbin/l_getidentity &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
